MVTSPLOT Przyk≈Çady

Posty przyk≈Çad z danymi symulacyjnymi

library("mvtsplot")
set.seed(971)
x1 <- matrix(-0.005 * (1:200) + rnorm(200 * 10), 200, 10)
x2 <- matrix(-0.005 * (1:200) + rnorm(200 * 10, mean = 2, sd = 2), 200, 10)
x <- cbind(x1, x2)
colnames(x) <- paste("X", 1:ncol(x))
g <- gl(2, 10)
mvtsplot(x, margin = FALSE, norm = "internal", group = g)

mvtsplot(x, margin = FALSE, norm = "global", group = g)

mvtsplot(x, group = g, levels = 7)

Ozon w USA

  • kryterialne zanieczyszczenie
  • dane pochodzƒÖ z systemu monitorowania jako≈õci powietrza EPA (Environmental Protection Agency)
  • sezonowo≈õƒá

# Load necessary libraries (if not already loaded)
library(mvtsplot)

# Load the ozone data
load("o3-data.RData")

# Filter the data to include only dates after "2002-01-01"
use <- xtime >= as.Date("2002-01-01")
xtime <- xtime[use]
o3 <- o3[use, ]

# Load the top 100 data and the county census data
use <- dget("top100.R")
o3 <- o3[, use]
cc <- dget("countycensus.R")

# Order the data based on latitude and change column names using fipsNames
ord <- order(cc[use, "lat"])
source("fipsNames.R")
colnames(o3) <- fipsNames(colnames(o3))
xtime <- as.Date(xtime, format="%Y-%m-%d")

# Create a multivariate time series plot for daily ozone with 11 levels
mvtsplot(o3[, ord], levels = 11, main = "Daily ozone")

load("component-data.RData")
sulfate <- sapply(compList, function(x) x[, "SULFATE"])
region <- dget("fips-region.R")
tab <- region$regionEW
names(tab) <- region$fips
EW <- tab[colnames(sulfate)]
source("fipsNames.R")
colnames(sulfate) <- fipsNames(colnames(sulfate))
mvtsplot(sulfate, group = EW, main = "Daily sulfate \n level")

# Assuming 'compList' contains 'nickel' and 'sulfate' data
nickel_bronx <- nickel[, "Bronx, NY", drop = FALSE]
sulfate_bronx <- sulfate[, "Bronx, NY", drop = FALSE]

# Merge the 'nickel' and 'sulfate' data for "Bronx, NY" into a two-column data frame
merged_data <- cbind(nickel_bronx, sulfate_bronx)
colnames(merged_data) <- c("nickel", "sulfate")

mvtsplot(merged_data, smooth.df =24,  main = "Daily sulfate and nickel in Bronx \n level normalized")


x <- compList[["36005"]]  ## Bronx
med <- apply(x, 2, median, na.rm = TRUE)
ord <- order(med, decreasing = TRUE)
use <- ord[1:40]
## Omit sulfur (5) so that we don't double count
mvtsplot(x[, use[-5]], rowstat = sum, smooth.df = 4 * 4, levels = 15, main = "Largest \n 40 components")
